Development of spontaneity and creativity. Handling roles. The essence of role behaviour. The use of drama techniques in solving different situations. Body as means of expression. Import of the extra-reality. Mixing drama with other creative methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To create prerequisites for the development of self-awareness.  To develop skills of finding different drama techniques in order to solve different situations and for self-help. To broaden understanding of role-based behaviour, the essence, meaning and the effect of the roles on people. To get to know different ways of using the voice and drama techniques in one's work.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Has team work skills and courage of self-expression;
Is able to take and change roles;
Is able to creatively use ones voice and different talents in a drama play;
Is able to coordinate a drama play;
Knows how to integrate drama into curriculum;
Knows how to compose a thematic speech and present it.
